Great question. Here's the optimal AdMob setup for Dynasty Manager:

AdMob Ad Unit Setup
You only need ONE ad unit type: Rewarded Video

Since all ads in Dynasty Manager are opt-in (player chooses to watch for a reward), rewarded video is the only format you need. This is also the highest-paying mobile ad format — typically $10-40 eCPM vs $1-5 for banners.

Step-by-step in AdMob Dashboard:
Create your app at admob.google.com

Add iOS app (link to App Store listing or enter bundle ID com.dynastymanager.app)
Add Android app (link to Play Store listing or enter package name)
Create ONE Rewarded ad unit per platform:

Ad unit name: Dynasty Manager - Rewarded
Reward type: reward (amount: 1)
Frequency cap: None (your code already handles limits via AD_REWARD_LIMITS — max 3/day per reward type)
eCPM floor: Leave at default initially
Copy the ad unit IDs (format: ca-app-pub-XXXXXXX/YYYYYYY) and replace the placeholders in src/utils/ads.ts:

REWARDED_AD_UNIT_IOS = 'ca-app-pub-YOUR_ID/YOUR_UNIT'
REWARDED_AD_UNIT_ANDROID = 'ca-app-pub-YOUR_ID/YOUR_UNIT'

Optimal Settings
Setting	Recommendation	Why
Ad format	Rewarded Video only	Highest eCPM, player-friendly, no interruptions
Mediation	Enable AdMob mediation	Higher fill rates by falling back to other networks
Networks	Add Meta Audience Network + Unity Ads as mediation sources	20-40% higher revenue vs AdMob alone
Frequency cap	Don't set in AdMob	Already capped in code (3/day per type, 5 types = 15 max/day)
eCPM floor	$5 initially, adjust after 2 weeks of data	Filters low-quality ads without hurting fill rate
Test mode	Use test ads during development	Already set: initializeForTesting: true in ads.ts — flip to false before release
Before Release Checklist
Flip initializeForTesting: false in src/utils/ads.ts
Add your real ad unit IDs
Set up AdMob app-ads.txt (required for monetization)
Add mediation partners (Meta + Unity Ads minimum)
Configure GDPR consent (required for EU users) — use Google UMP SDK
Run npx cap sync to update native projects
Revenue Estimate
With rewarded video at ~$15 eCPM average:

Free users watching 2-3 ads/day = ~$0.03-0.05/user/day
1,000 DAU = ~$30-50/day, ~$900-1500/month
This supplements IAP revenue from Pro upgrades and cosmetic packs
Don't Bother With
Banner ads — Low eCPM ($1-3), clutters the mobile UI, feels cheap for a premium game
Interstitial ads — Interrupts gameplay, high churn risk, goes against your "player-first" philosophy
App Open ads — Same issue, annoying on launch
The current architecture is already optimal — one rewarded unit shared across all 5 reward placements, with per-type daily limits controlled in code. Just create the ad unit, plug in the IDs, and you're live.
